{
  "stem": "10272.1",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My name is Emil Jacoby.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "E-M-I-L J-A-C-O-B-Y.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I was born Jacobovitz, J-A-C-O-B-O-V-I-T-Z.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I was born on October the 10th, 1923.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I was born in a village named Terebla, T-E-R-E-B-L-A, Terebla, in an area called, at that time, Carpatoros, which belonged to Czechoslovakia.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My father's name-- he was born Mendel Jacobovitz.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] His father's name was [?",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Lieb ?] Jacobovitz, and his mother was [?",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Chendel ?].",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They lived in a very, very small village, [?",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Chandrov ?], not far from Bushtina, where we lived after my father married my mother.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They moved from Terebla to Bushtina.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Bushtina's a bigger city, a bigger town, than all  those small villages.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "My father, as a young boy, he [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] emigrated to the United States to help his family.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And he stayed in the United States as a naturalized citizen, American citizen.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "He stayed in Chicago, Illinois for almost 20 years.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I don't remember the exact years, but between 15 and 20 years he was there. 17, maybe 18, years.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "He came back after World War I to visit his hometown.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And he married-- it was before World War I-- to visit his hometown.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And he married a girl from Terebla by the name of Leia.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And he went back to the United States to take her out, to send her the papers.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "In the meantime, war broke out-- World War I broke out-- and he couldn't get her home to take her out.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And she wouldn't go with him back to America.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "She kept him there in Terebla.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And he remained there-- he married her and he went over to Bushtina, which was a bigger town, to settle down.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He brought home a lot of dollars, which made him a very well-to-do person in that time.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So he built his own house, his own business-- a wholesale business-- and he was doing very well for a while.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But then later, when I grew up and I start go to school, business went down.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was a wholesale business selling wheat for the small stores in the area.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He came to buy big bags of wheat and flour.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Then he had, also, a general store.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And also, he was having a farm, which people working with cows and horses.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So when he went bankrupt because people couldn't pay up the debts for buying on credit, so just gave up the wholesale, other big business, and he remained with this general store.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The school was in the city by the name of Chust, C-H-U-S-T-- Chust.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was a large city.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I went there.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I started in September, 1st of September, to go to school, but I'm not sure I made two months in the school.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I had to go there Friday evening, to Chust, because I had to go to high school on Saturday, too, on the sabbath, in order not to violate sabbath.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I was raised in an orthodox religious family.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I had to go there and sleep over in Chust in my aunt's house.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Aunt's name was Miriam.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Last name was [?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Leibowitz ?].",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I'm not sure it's [?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Leibowitz ?].",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "That's what I think, it [? was Leibowitz. ?]",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "When Hitler met Chamberlain, the prime minister of Britain, and Deladier, prime minister of France, they agreed to sacrifice part of Czechoslovakia in order for Hitler not to invade Czechoslovakia.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "That was the crises of that time which broke out, and Jewish communities were very concerned at that time that Hitler is going to invade Czechoslovakia.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And Jews were, I remember, in the synagogue.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Their concern was noticed during the prayers in the synagogue when they were crying loud out during to prayer on sabbath-- oh, God, help us to overcome these difficult times.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They were very concerned.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But then, after a few sermons, which the rabbi-- which his name was [INAUDIBLE]-- came, and also the rabbi from [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And big rabbis used come to our town and held sermons.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And they would touch this crisis during the sermon, giving them hope, telling them not to fear this terrible thing which is going on.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Because first of all, he tried to make people to relax and to calm down, telling them, like, God always came to help of the Jewish people, not to let them get destroyed, like Haman during Purim, making miracles all the time in history.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So they would not fear.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But he would always mention that we have to fear more a danger not from Hitler, he says.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Hitler is a politician, and he has to make this noise about anti-Semitism because he wants to-- actually, what he wants to do is not kill Jews, the rabbi would say.",
      "word_count": 31
    }
  ],
